---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 4
  Paragraph: 33
Title: In The World Of Men
---
Yen Ho, who had been appointed tutor to the crown prince, son of Duke
Ling of Wei, went to consult Ch'u Po-yu. "Here is this man who by
nature is lacking in virtue. If I let him go on with his unruliness I
will endanger the state. If I try to impose some rule on him, I will
endanger myself. He knows enough to recognize the faults of others, but
he doesn't know his own faults. What can I do with a man like this?"
